** About us **

Disaster Relief Australia (DRA) brings hope to communities devastated by
disaster. We unite the skills and experience of military veterans, emergency
responders and motivated civilians to deploy Disaster Relief Teams around
Australia and the world. With our army of dedicated volunteers, we respond to
disasters and deliver support to those in need.

At the heart of our mission is a commitment to serving those in need, powered
by cutting-edge technology and a team of passionate IT professionals. We're on
the lookout for a dynamic Power Apps, Power Automate, and Virtual Agents
Developer to join our Brisbane-based team on a part-time basis. This role is a
unique opportunity to harness your technical expertise to make a tangible
difference in communities across Australia and beyond.

** The Role **

As our Power Apps, Power Automate, and Virtual Agents Developer, you'll play a
pivotal role in enhancing our operational capabilities through custom
solutions that streamline processes, improve efficiency, and elevate our
disaster relief efforts. Your passion for technology and desire to contribute
to a meaningful cause will drive innovation within our organisation, directly
impacting our ability to respond to crises.

** Key Responsibilities **

  * Design, develop, and implement solutions using Microsoft Power Apps, Power Automate, and Virtual Agents (Copilots) to address complex business challenges. 
  * Collaborate with cross-functional teams to understand requirements and deliver high-impact applications that improve disaster response operations. 
  * Provide expert guidance on the capabilities and best use of Microsoft Power Platform technologies to maximise organisational effectiveness. 
  * Conduct training sessions for staff to ensure optimal adoption and utilisation of developed applications. 
  * Stay abreast of the latest advancements in Microsoft Power Platform technologies and explore innovative ways to apply them within the disaster relief context. 

** About You **

  * Profound knowledge and hands-on experience with Microsoft Power Apps, Power Automate, and Virtual Agents (Copilots). 
  * A strong portfolio demonstrating previous success in developing and implementing solutions that have driven efficiency and impact. 
  * Excellent problem-solving skills and the ability to think creatively to overcome challenges. 
  * Exceptional communication and collaboration abilities, with a knack for explaining complex technical concepts in an accessible manner. 
  * A passion for leveraging technology to make a positive difference in the world, ideally with an interest or background in non-profit work or disaster relief. 
  * Relevant certifications in Microsoft Power Platform technologies are highly regarded. 
  * Prior experience working with Defence will be highly regarded. 

** Why Join Us? **

  * Make a Difference: Your work directly contributes to our mission of providing disaster relief, offering an unparalleled sense of purpose and fulfilment. 
  * Innovate for Good: Use cutting-edge technology to solve real-world problems and innovate in ways that have a tangible impact on our disaster response capabilities. 
  * Join a Community: Be part of a dedicated team that values collaboration, innovation, and the power of technology to change lives. 

** How to Apply **

If you're ready to use your technical talents to make a real difference, we
want to hear from you! Submit your application, including a resume and a cover
letter detailing your experience with Microsoft Power Platform technologies
and why you're passionate about joining Disaster Relief Australia.

Please apply directly to Disaster Relief Australia by going to:

** https://disasterreliefaus.elmotalent.com.au/careers/DRA/job/view/26 **

and clicking the ‘Apply’ button.

